\subsection{Import of microarray data and initial quality control}

\subsubsection{Importing CEL files}
The microrarray analysis of Affymetrix arrays starts with CEL files. These are the result
of processing of the raw image files using the Affymetrix software and contain
estimated probe intensity values. Each CEL file contains data on the intensity at each
probe on the chip, as well as some other quantities.
We collect the information about the CEL files
we want to import and then save them in  the variable \Robject{rawData}.

The followng code results in a character vector with the paths to the
CEL files we want to import. the function \Rfunction{read.celfiles}
from the \Biocpkg{oligo} can be
used to import the files. The package automatically usees
\Biocannopkg{pd.hugene.1.0.st} as the chip annotation package.

We specifiy our \Rclass{AnnotatedDataFrame}

<<importCelfiles, results='hide', eval=TRUE, dependson="getSDRF">>=
celfolder <- rawDataDir
cels <- list.celfiles(path = celfolder, pattern="*.CEL")

rawData <- read.celfiles(filenames = file.path(rawDataDir, cels),
                         verbose = FALSE, phenoData = SDRF)

validObject(rawData)
#save(rawData, file = "rawData.RData")
@

We inspect the raw data and remove some uninteresting phenoData columns and retain
only those that are related to the experimental factors. (IDs of the individuals,
disease of the individual and the mucosa type)

